<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idcb7acaeb-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70" identifier="/us/usc/t49/s32301"><num value="32301">§ 32301.</num><heading> Definitions</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">In this chapter—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idcb7acaec-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70" identifier="/us/usc/t49/s32301/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> “crash avoidance” means preventing or mitigating a crash;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idcb7acaed-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70" identifier="/us/usc/t49/s32301/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> “crashworthiness” means the protection a passenger motor vehicle gives its passengers against personal injury or death from a motor vehicle accident; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idcb7acaee-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70" identifier="/us/usc/t49/s32301/3"><num value="3">(3)</num><content> “damage susceptibility” means the susceptibility of a passenger motor vehicle to damage in a motor vehicle accident.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="idcb7acaef-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70">(<ref href="/us/pl/103/272/s1/e">Pub. L. 103–272, § 1(e)</ref>, <date date="1994-07-05">July 5, 1994</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/108/1035">108 Stat. 1035</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/112/141/dC/tI/s31305/a">Pub. L. 112–141, div. C, title I, § 31305(a)</ref>, <date date="2012-07-06">July 6, 2012</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/126/765">126 Stat. 765</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
